The sun sets behind the Statue of Liberty in New York City. 

The red tinge is indicative of the environmental damage caused by wildfires in the US. It occurs as a result of dense smoke particles in the upper reaches of the atmosphere mixing with sunlight. 

#newyork #environment #sun #statueofliberty #climatechange 

REUTERS/Bjoern Kils/New York Media Boat

Momiji Nishiya of Japan celebrates her gold medal in skateboarding at the Tokyo Olympic Games. 

At just 13-years-old, she's one of the youngest gold medal winners ever. After her win she said: 'It's not right to think, well you have to study, you can't go skating because skating is for boys, I think skateboarding is for everyone.' 

#skateboarding #skating #sport #olympics #tokyo2020 

REUTERS/Lucy Nicholson
